## Tools and Technologies

| Tool               | Purpose                                           |
|--------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
| Power BI Desktop   | Data modeling, DAX measures, and dashboard design |
| Power Query        | Data cleaning and transformation                  |
| CSV Files          | Raw source data                                   |
| DAX                | Custom KPI calculations and percentage metrics    |

---

## Data Source

The data used in this project was sourced from [Maven Analytics](https://www.mavenanalytics.io/), a platform offering real-world datasets for data analysis practice and portfolio projects. [file:1]

Full credit goes to Maven Analytics for providing the dataset. Please refer to their website for data usage terms.

---

## Key Insights

- Over 2 million flights were analyzed, with 41% experiencing delays and only 1% cancelled.   
- Atlanta, Chicago, and Dallas–Fort Worth are the busiest airports by total flight volume.   
- United Airlines has the highest delay rate at 53%, while SkyWest Airlines has the lowest at 35%.   
- Weather and airline or carrier issues are the dominant causes of flight cancellations.   
- Cancellation rates fluctuate by day of the week, with certain weekdays showing noticeably higher rates. 

---

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- [Power BI Desktop](https://powerbi.microsoft.com/desktop/) (free); latest version recommended. 

### Steps

1. Clone or download this repository.  
2. Place the CSV data files inside the `data/` folder.  
3. Open `Flight_Status_Dashboard.pbix` in Power BI Desktop.   
4. If prompted, update the data source path to point to your local `data/` folder.   
5. Select **Refresh** to load the data. 

